# Amplify Environment Variable Safety

**APP_ID: `d1p01xz65d2ex4`** | **REGION: `us-east-2`**

## CRITICAL — `aws amplify update-app --environment-variables` REPLACES ALL vars. It does NOT merge.

This mistake has wiped env vars TWICE (once in Carmen, once in Gigler). NEVER let it happen again.

## Mandatory Workflow — Every Single Time

### 1. BACKUP FIRST
```bash
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-2 bash scripts/backup-amplify-env.sh d1p01xz65d2ex4
```

### 2. FETCH ALL existing env vars
```bash
EXISTING=$(aws amplify get-app --app-id d1p01xz65d2ex4 --region us-east-2 --query 'app.environmentVariables' --output json)
```

### 3. MERGE new var(s) into the full set (Python one-liner)
```bash
MERGED=$(echo "$EXISTING" | python3 -c "
import sys, json
existing = json.load(sys.stdin)
existing['NEW_VAR'] = 'new_value'
print(json.dumps(existing))
")
```

### 4. PUSH the COMPLETE merged set
```bash
aws amplify update-app --app-id d1p01xz65d2ex4 --region us-east-2 --environment-variables "$MERGED"
```

### 5. VERIFY the count matches or exceeds the previous count
```bash
aws amplify get-app --app-id d1p01xz65d2ex4 --region us-east-2 --query 'app.environmentVariables | keys(@) | length(@)'
```

## NEVER Do This
```bash
# DANGEROUS — wipes all other vars!
aws amplify update-app --app-id d1p01xz65d2ex4 --environment-variables '{"ONLY_ONE_VAR":"value"}'
```

## Recovery
Backups are stored in `.amplify-env-backups/` with timestamps.
```bash
aws amplify update-app --app-id d1p01xz65d2ex4 --region us-east-2 \
  --environment-variables "$(cat .amplify-env-backups/env-backup-TIMESTAMP.json)"
```
